                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa ʾaślәṭi, Lectionary for the entire year (fols. 1va-67vb)&#xD;
                     II) Bārәkanna ʾәgziʾo… “Bless us, O Lord…” (Blessing prayer) (fol.
                     68ra-68vb)&#xD; &#xD; Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="1va" to="67vb"/>
                     <title>Maṣḥafa ʾaslǝṭi</title>
                     <note>The collection is called Maṣḥafa ʾaslǝṭi in the incipit of Text I (<locus target="#9ra">9ra</locus>).</note>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="1va" to="67vb"/>
                        <title ref="LIT1917Mashaf">Maṣḥafa ʾaślәṭi</title>                                                
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <locus from="68ra" to="68vb"/>
                        <title ref="LIT5655BarekannaEgzio"/>
                     </msItem>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#67vb">67vb</locus>: ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸመኒ፡ ለዘቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ በዳኅና፡
                        ወበሰላም፡ ወምስለ፡ ጸሐፊሁ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ወአባሲ፡ ገብረ፡ መድኅን፡ ወምስለ፡ ገብሩ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ምስለ፡ እመቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡
                        ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ተፈጸመ፡ ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ በ፲፱፻፴፮፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ተጽሐፈ፡ በዘበነ፡ ሉቃስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡
                        በዘበነ፡ ንጉ [<locus target="#68ra">68ra</locus>] ሥነ፡ ሃይለ፡ ሥላሴ። <note>The note mentions
                        the name of a scribe, Gabra Madḫǝn, and the names of ʾAragāwi and Walatta
                        Giyorgis who most probably are the donors. The date <date when="1944">1936 A.M. (=1943/44 A.D.)</date>
                        and the reference to King Ḫāyla Śǝllāse I (1930-74) were added probably by the
                        same hand.</note> 
                     </colophon>
